# Arduino Digital Hourglass

An interactive digital hourglass using two 8x8 LED matrices, an accelerometer, and a buzzer. Users can set various time modes via a physical button.

## ðŸ“„ About this Project

This project simulates the mechanics of a traditional hourglass. By tilting the device (detected via the ADXL335 accelerometer), digital "sand grains" fall from the top matrix to the bottom one. When the time is up, an alarm sounds.

### Copyright & Credits

* **Original Author:** EDISON SCIENCE CORNER
* **Modifications & Optimization:** P.M. Bloemendaal
